    "analysis": "Metric analysis: no metric anomalies found in the incident window for the five candidate services. Trace analysis (previous run) produced many trace error_rate groups but all had global_p95 = global_p5 = 0.0 and observed values = 0.0 (a telemetry/threshold artifact), so traces were inconclusive. Log analysis: real anomalies were found in log.row_count for ts-auth-service, ts-order-service, ts-route-service, and ts-travel-service — each showing multiple low points (drops in row_count) during 2024-01-24T04:37:00Z to 2024-01-24T05:01:00Z and a few brief high spikes. log.error_count appears to be all zeros (artifact) and should be ignored. The simultaneous drops across multiple services suggest an upstream traffic/ingestion reduction or a logging-forwarder issue rather than an isolated resource fault in a single service. To localize root cause among the candidate services, we must inspect trace call/row_count traces (trace row_count / from_root.row_count / trace.from_<service>.row_count) to identify which service is the most downstream faulty service in call chains. Proceed to targeted trace row_count anomaly detection.",
